<h2>
    Rules for Naming
</h2>
<p>
    Naming conventions are like most other programming languages, expect 
    a dollar sign<code>$</code> can be put as the first character of the name. Underscores
    <code>_</code> or lowercase letters are also acceptable first characters, and numbers can 
    be in the name, just not as first characters. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">
int age;  // Best Practice 
int _age; // _ as first letter
int $age;  // $ as first letter
int age_1; // number in name
</code></pre>

<p>
    Use descriptive names for variables and avoid single letter variables 
    like <code>x</code> or <code>y</code>: they are dry and nondescriptive. Use 
    a name that represents what's inside the variable. 
</p>